  <!-- Detailed Analysis -->
  <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-100 mb-4">Detailed Comparison</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">European Tutor Availability</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Both platforms have built strong European tutor networks over the years. Preply's larger overall tutor base of 50,000+ means you will find tutors from virtually every European country, including Germany, France, Spain, Italy, Poland, the Netherlands, and Scandinavia. Verbling's 10,000+ tutors include a significant European presence, particularly from Spain and Latin America. Both platforms allow you to filter tutors by country and time zone, making it easy to find a European tutor who fits your schedule.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Pricing</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Preply holds a clear advantage on pricing, with tutors available from around $5/hour compared to Verbling's typical starting price of $12/hour. This makes Preply especially attractive for learners on a budget who want to practice frequently. Preply's optional subscription model offers additional savings for regular learners. Verbling's higher price floor tends to attract more experienced or certified tutors, so the extra cost may be worth it if you prioritize credentials and experience.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Lesson Structure and Platform Features</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Preply provides a more structured learning experience, with built-in curriculum materials, conversation topics organized by level, and a vocabulary trainer. The platform includes a whiteboard for writing practice and lesson recording so you can review sessions later. Verbling takes a more flexible, conversation-led approach where tutors customize lessons to your goals. Both platforms offer business English and exam prep materials, though Preply's structured curriculum may appeal more to learners who want a clear progression path.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Flexibility and Cancellation</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Both platforms offer flexible scheduling and cancellation policies. Preply allows cancellations up to 24 hours in advance for a full refund, with shorter notice periods available depending on individual tutor settings. Verbling typically accepts cancellations 12 to 24 hours before the scheduled session. Neither platform requires a subscription, giving you the freedom to book one-off lessons without committing to a monthly plan.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Verdict Box -->
  <div class="bg-emerald-900/30 border-2 border-emerald-500 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-300 mb-2">Our Verdict</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Choose <strong>Preply</strong> if you are on a budget, want the largest tutor selection, and prefer structured lesson materials. Choose <strong>Verbling</strong> if you prioritize native English speaker access, flexible conversation-based lessons, and a straightforward pay-per-lesson model without subscription pressure.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm"><strong>Best value:</strong> Preply. <strong>Best for native speakers:</strong> Verbling. Both are legitimate, well-established platforms trusted by thousands of learners.</p>
  </div>

